# IssueForge environment template
#
# Copy to `.env` and fill in. `.env` is gitignored, so secrets stay local.
# Every value here can also be set in the project YAML config; precedence is
# YAML < env < CLI.
#
# Easiest way to populate this file: run `issueforge init` (or `bootstrap`).
# It will copy a template config and set AGENT_WORKER_CONFIG for you.

# ─── Which project YAML to load ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Path to the project-specific YAML overlay. Recommended: keep one YAML per
# business repo and switch by editing this.
#
# Start from a clean template:
#   AGENT_WORKER_CONFIG=configs/examples/generic-python.yaml
#
# Or copy the example to your own file:
#   cp configs/examples/generic-python.yaml configs/myproject.yaml
#   AGENT_WORKER_CONFIG=configs/myproject.yaml
AGENT_WORKER_CONFIG=configs/examples/generic-python.yaml

# ─── Project root (rare) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# By default `issueforge init` writes the YAML into your current working
# directory. Set this to anchor relative paths (configs/, .env, runs/) to a
# specific directory regardless of where you invoke the CLI.
# AGENT_WORKER_PROJECT_ROOT=/absolute/path/to/your/issueforge/checkout

# ─── GitHub ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Token used by `gh` CLI / GitHub REST. Leave blank to reuse the credentials
# from `gh auth login` — that's the recommended path. Setting GITHUB_TOKEN
# explicitly is mainly useful in CI / docker contexts where `gh auth login`
# isn't available.
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# ─── Coding agent (default executor) ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Override path to the cursor-agent binary if it isn't on PATH. The default
# value just looks up `cursor-agent`; uncomment if yours lives elsewhere.
# CURSOR_AGENT_BIN=/usr/local/bin/cursor-agent
#
# Or use Claude / Codex instead of Cursor — set executor.default: claude_code
# or codex in your YAML and (optionally) point at the binary here:
# CLAUDE_BIN=/usr/local/bin/claude
# CODEX_BIN=/usr/local/bin/codex

# ─── Temporal ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
TEMPORAL_HOST=localhost:7233
TEMPORAL_NAMESPACE=default
# Task queue name; must match between client and worker.
TEMPORAL_TASK_QUEUE=issueforge

# ─── docker compose (only if you use docker-compose.yml) ─────────────────────
# Absolute host path to the *business repo* the worker should operate on.
# Required when using `docker compose up -d worker`. Must match
# `repo.local_path` in your project YAML.
# WORKER_BUSINESS_REPO_PATH=/absolute/path/to/your/business/repo

# ─── Artifacts / state ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ARTIFACT_ROOT=./runs
LANGGRAPH_CHECKPOINT_DB=./checkpoints/langgraph.sqlite

# ─── Feishu (optional, Phase 4 stub) ─────────────────────────────────────────
# FEISHU_VERIFY_TOKEN=
# FEISHU_ENCRYPT_KEY=
# FEISHU_APP_ID=
# FEISHU_APP_SECRET=
